# Remote Network Node - Environment Variables Example
# Copy this file to .env and fill in your actual values
# IMPORTANT: Never commit .env to git! (it's in .gitignore)

# ============================================================================
# KEYSTORE PASSPHRASE
# ============================================================================
# Passphrase for the encrypted keystore that protects your node's private keys
#
# Security Recommendations:
# - Use a strong passphrase (minimum 12 characters recommended)
# - Include mix of uppercase, lowercase, numbers, and special characters
# - Never share this passphrase or commit it to version control
# - Store securely (password manager, encrypted vault, etc.)
#
# If not set, the node will prompt for passphrase interactively on startup
# This is required for background/automated node operation
KEYSTORE_PASSPHRASE=

# ============================================================================
# DEPLOYMENT EXAMPLES
# ============================================================================

# Development (local machine):
# KEYSTORE_PASSPHRASE=my-dev-passphrase-123

# Production (server deployment):
# KEYSTORE_PASSPHRASE=Tr0ng!P@ssw0rd#F0r$Pr0d

# Docker/Container (read from secrets management):
# KEYSTORE_PASSPHRASE=${DOCKER_SECRET_KEYSTORE_PASS}

# ============================================================================
# OPTIONAL: CUSTOM CONFIG PATH
# ============================================================================
# Uncomment to override the default config directory location
# Default: ~/.config/remote-network/
# CONFIG_PATH=/path/to/custom/config

# ============================================================================
# NOTES
# ============================================================================
#
# 1. How to use this file:
#    $ cp .env.example .env
#    $ nano .env  # Edit and set your passphrase
#    $ chmod 600 .env  # Secure permissions (owner read/write only)
#
# 2. The config file (configs) reads environment variables:
#    keystore_passphrase = KEYSTORE_PASSPHRASE
#    This means the config value will be replaced with the env var value
#
# 3. Priority order for passphrase:
#    1. Environment variable (KEYSTORE_PASSPHRASE in .env)
#    2. Config file value (if not using env var)
#    3. --passphrase-file flag
#    4. Interactive prompt
#
# 4. First-time setup:
#    - On first run, you'll be prompted to create a passphrase
#    - After creating, add it to .env for future automated startups
#    - Your keystore will be created at: ~/.local/share/remote-network/keystore.dat
#
# 5. Security best practices:
#    - Backup your keystore.dat file regularly
#    - Store passphrase in a password manager
#    - Use different passphrases for dev/staging/production
#    - Rotate passphrases periodically (requires creating new keystore)
#
# 6. Background startup example:
#    $ source .env
#    $ nohup remote-network-node start > /dev/null 2>&1 &
#
# 7. SystemD service example:
#    Add EnvironmentFile=/path/to/.env in your service file
#
